         <abstract>
            <p>Spion is an adventure game intended as a teaching tool for intermediate and advanced college German. It recognizes and 'understands' a small subset of German large enough to allow a student to play the game. To win the game, players are required to communicate with a fictitious agent in complete, correct German sentences. The version of the game described here was written in PROLOG as the natural outgrowth of a series of earlier programs. The program runs on an IBM-PC or compatible and is available at no cost for noncommercial purposes.</p>
         </abstract>
